145 2026, and as provided in subsection 6 of this section for
146 all calendar years beginning on or after January 1, 2027:
147 (a) For real property in subclass (1), nineteen
148 percent;
149 (b) For real property in subclass (2), twelve percent;
150 and
151 (c) For real property in subclass (3), thirty-two
152 percent.
153 (2) A taxpayer may apply to the county assessor, or,
154 if not located within a county, then the assessor of such
155 city, for the reclassification of such taxpayer's real
156 property if the use or purpose of such real property is
